The course provides an overview of technological platforms for international data processing, as well as their legal framework.Objectives/eesmärkid:  The objective of the course is to address the infrastructure of cross-border data exchange and applicable legal frameworks and analyze relevant practices, issues and developments in international data processing.Learning outcomes/õpiväljund:  Students will develop the ability to understand technical and legal preconditions and requirements of international data processing, solve relevant legal problems and assess business and political risk resulting from international data processing models and interests. Students will be able to: * understand the basic infrastructure and technologies of cross-border exchange of data; * understand the regulation and regulatory issues that have emerged in relation to the development and use of this infrastructure; * understand the complexity of balancing different values and interests pertaining to the development and use of this infrastructure. * understand the political, legal and technical strategies of achieving different values and interests pertaining to the development and use of this infrastructure.
